<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Daria Trainor — software engineer, specification thinker, AI pragmatist."
	pubDate={new Date('2026-03-14')}
>
	<p>
		I'm Daria Trainor, a senior software engineer at nib Group in Newcastle, Australia. Originally
		from Kharkiv, Ukraine, I've spent 20+ years working across software engineering, QA, business
		analysis, and project management.
	</p>

	<p>
		That mix of experience — having been both the person writing the code and the person writing the
		requirements — shapes how I think about software. I've seen firsthand how the gap between
		"what to build" and "how to build it" is where most projects succeed or fail.
	</p>

	<p>
		Right now I'm interested in how AI is changing the craft of software engineering. Not the hype
		— the real, practical shift in what it means to be a developer when code production is
		increasingly automated. I think the answer has more to do with judgement, specification, and
		clear thinking than most people expect.
	</p>

	<p>
		This blog is where I write about that.
	</p>
</Layout>
